# MSB Work Order System — DB-First SOP (Final v2)
**Project:** MSB Database (Production Ops)  
**Owner:** Greg (Production Crew)  
**Audience:** Managers + Volunteers (separate operating sections)  
**Scope:** Design + operational workflow only (NO SQL/DDL here).  
**Outcome:** Postgres is the single source of truth for work orders (create/assign/complete/history), with legacy Google Sheets imported.

---

## 1) What we are doing (Decisions Locked)
### 1.1 DB is the source of truth
- All work orders live in the MSB Production Database.
- All updates happen in the DB:
  - create
  - assign
  - completion
  - notes / comments
- Google Form/Sheets are legacy history and (optionally) intake only. Once DB intake is live, Google can be retired.

### 1.2 “Done flag” is not needed
- We will not store a separate `done_flag`.
- Open vs Completed is derived:
  - **Open**: `date_completed` is NULL
  - **Completed**: `date_completed` is NOT NULL
- Completed items must have `date_completed` populated.

### 1.3 Priority is split into two independent fields
Legacy “Priority” was overloaded. In the DB we store:
- **Urgency** (optional): triage / “do now”
- **Target Year** (optional): planning / “do during 2026 season”
Either can be null, and either/both can be set.

### 1.4 Work location is unified
We must support:
- Park stages (ref.stage)
- Non-stage locations (workshop, office, command center, etc.)
We will create a unified `ref.work_area` and work orders will point to `work_area_id`.

### 1.5 People + permissions live in ref.person (locked)
- We have **only `ref.person`** (no separate `ref.user`).
- Manager permissions are stored in `ref.person` (manager boolean lives there).
- Email lookup and identity are handled via `ref.person`.

### 1.6 Anyone authenticated can create a work order
- Any person who can authenticate in `my.sheboyganlights.org` can create a work order.
- Assignment is manager-controlled (see Section 5).

