## 2) Tables Needed (Minimum v1)
### 2.1 Reference tables
1) **ref.work_area** (NEW)
- Canonical list of places where work happens.
- Supports stage-backed and non-stage areas.
- Stage-backed areas reference `ref.stage`.

2) **ref.task_type** (NEW)
- Canonical list: Repair, Build, Setup, Design, etc.

3) **ref.person** (EXISTS, includes manager boolean)
- Canonical people list (email + manager flag).

4) **ref.stage** (EXISTS)
- Canonical stage list (used by work_area when type=STAGE).

> Optional (recommended soon, but not required for v1):
- **ref.work_order_status** (NEW) if we want more workflow states than open/completed.

### 2.2 Operational tables
1) **ops.work_order** (NEW)
- Main record for all work items (repairs + long-term plans).

2) **ops.work_order_assignee** (NEW, recommended)
- Supports 0..N assignees per work order.

> Optional but valuable:
- **ops.work_order_comment** (recommended)
  - Captures “what was done” and ongoing notes without overwriting history.

