## 4) Import Plan (Google Sheets → DB)
### 4.1 Source sheets
- “To do” (open work orders)
- “Completed” (closed work orders history)

### 4.2 Combine into one DB table
- Both tabs import into `ops.work_order`.
- Open vs Completed derived from `date_completed`.

### 4.3 Completed-tab validation rule (critical)
- Completed rows should have `date_completed`.
- If any Completed rows have a blank completion date, we must fill it during import.

**Rule for missing completion dates found on Completed tab:**
1) If `date_added` exists → set `date_completed = date_added`
2) Else → set `date_completed = import_timestamp`
Also record that the date was backfilled (import audit / note).

### 4.4 Preserve and parse legacy “Priority”
- Keep exact raw value in `legacy_priority_raw`.
- Soft-parse into:
  - target_year (if it looks like a year, e.g., >= 2020)
  - urgency_code (if it looks like P1 / 1 / 2 / etc.)
- If it doesn’t parse cleanly, leave both null and keep legacy_priority_raw.

