## 5) Creation, Assignment, Completion Rules (DB UI behavior)
### 5.1 Creating a work order (any authenticated user)
- Any authenticated user may create.
- Fields available to all creators:
  - work_area, task_type, problem, notes, photo_url, target_year, urgency
  - (display link if available)
- Default assignment: **unassigned**.

### 5.2 Assignment (manager-controlled)
- Only **managers** (ref.person.manager = true) can assign work orders.
- Managers can assign:
  - at creation time
  - or later during triage
- Non-managers cannot set assignees.

### 5.3 Completing a work order (button behavior)
We will implement a **Complete** button in the UI.

When clicked:
- Set `date_completed = now()`
- Set `completed_by_person_id` based on the authenticated user (email → ref.person lookup)
- Prompt for “what was done”:
  - either fill `completion_notes`
  - or create a completion comment entry (if comments table exists)

If the user lacks a matching `ref.person` record, completion should be blocked (or logged) — we don’t want “unknown completed_by”.

